@genejchan They are building a baseline for how cheap this car is to operate at scale. They are also finishing off the AI that is driving the car, making sure it doesn't make any mistakes while tuning it up to make it smoother.

Furthermore, they are validating the manufacturing process. With Tesla, it usually takes a few thousand cars before they shake out all the problems in the supply chain with various componentry. They want to resolve those issues before they ship the first unit to a consumer.

This is going to drive a lot of people around and build a new American brand. It is going to be dramatic when it happens, but they need to test it first and tune it up as much as possible.

